<font color="#FF0000">THE COWARD'S SONG</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 26 10:34:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
He's not the typical American boy from the typical town,<br>
     And his only God is his own sweet ass,<br>
Hidden neath an intelect's gown.<br><br>
The food, the clothes, the very nice home,<br>
    And of course a car and college too,<br>
His type  got it all risk free--<br>
     Thanks to the likes of  me and you. <br><br>
I wondered where they got the idea,  <br>
     That &quot;having it all&quot; is their just due,<br>
 When I realized they'd always got it all--<br>
    Thanks to the likes of  me------and you!I  <br><br>
Yes, the cowards are now on the offensive,<br>
      (Hear their cries of girlish delight,)<br>
They have the courage to attack their own soldiers,<br>
    Its our nations enemies that they never fight!  <br><br>
Willing to make sacrifices means--<br>
     Putting our ass on the line in those years,<br>
Just so that he and his generation<br>
   Might have the laughter without all the tears. <br>
 <br>
Yes, the cowards have been living the good life,<br>
    They've never sacrificed at all,<br>
Laughing, joking and sneering,<br>
    When their cowards shadow falls on our Wall.<br><br>
Yes, he snees at all of our sacarfices,<br>
     His self love know no shame,<br>
And lacks the small amount of courage,<br>
     To reveal his own name.<br><br>
But I'll speak no more of stay-behinds,<br>
         Nor the results of  their &quot;Booty.&quot;<br>
The flag still flies and the bugle calls:<br>
     For men of Honor and Duty.<br><br>
 <br><br>
 
